❤️ GIVEAWAY: supporting the Monterey Park community ❤️
.
@shareyourasianstory was founded in 2021 to combat anti-Asian hate by sharing the stories of creatives in our diverse and resilient community and showing that we are not a faceless monolith. We are saddened by the horrible shooting in Monterey Park this weekend and want to continue supporting our community by hosting this giveaway.
.
For every donation to the Monterey Park Lunar New Year Victims Fund (organized by @advancingjusticesocal @stopaapihate @asianpaccommfund @aafstl @chinatownservicecenter @standwithasianamericans @goldhouseco @aapiequityalliance and Ann Wang), you’ll receive one entry to win the following below:

❤️1 original art print from @the_illustrienne + 1 surprise extra print
🧡1 original art print from @sandrahsuart 
💛1 art print, 1 postcard, and 1 signed copy of ENLY AND THE BUSKIN’ BLUES (written by @jennieliuliu , cover by Michelle) from @michellieart
🤍2 original art prints from @beck_lines 
.
We mourn for the Monterey Park community and continue to fight for a world where we can celebrate our cultures without fearing for our safety. 
.
Please DM @shareyourasianstory, or any of our cohosts @sandrahsuart , @beck_lines , @the_illustrienne , or @michellieart with proof of your donation. This is open until February 1, after which a winner will be chosen at random. All prints will be shipped separately at no cost to the winner.
.
➡️Link to the fund: https://tinyurl.com/mp-lny-fund
.
.
.

Those Sunday at 1pm PST, our guest on Share Your Asian Story will be Dr. Colin Zhu @thechefdoc ! 

Please join me and my cohosts @the_illustrienne and @beck_lines as we ask Colin to share his Asian story. ❤️💛🧡

Dr. Colin Zhu is Board-Certified in family practice/OMT and lifestyle medicine. Passionate about the intersection of medicine, food, and nutrition, Dr. Zhu trained as a chef and a health coach at the Natural Gourmet Institute for Health & Culinary Arts and the Institute for Integrative Nutrition following the completion of his medical degree. To share his unique blend of medical knowledge with a wider audience, Dr. Zhu launched TheChefDoc in 2017, an online wellness and lifestyle education platform which has been featured in several publications. Dr. Zhu is an international speaker, the author of "Thrive Medicine: How To Cultivate Your Desires and Elevate Your Life,“ and the podcast host of Thrive Bites in which he interviews the latest health and wellness experts about incorporating a plant-powered lifestyle, enhancing emotional wellness, and creating a thriving mindset! He is also the creator/director of a self-educational masterclass series called The THR5 Formula™ where he combines inspiration, education, and practical tools on how to THRIVE! Here you will learn the 5 To THR5™ Pillars: Food As Medicine, Functional Fitness, Relationships, Community, & Emotional Resilience! Currently, based in the Southern California area and has a virtual lifestyle medical practice called TheChefDoc Lifestyle Medicine. 

#shareyourasianstory #asianamerican #veryasian #watercolorportrait #lifestylemedicine

On this International Women’s Day, I wanted to take a moment to celebrate and appreciate all the amazing women I’ve had the privilege to interview and paint for Share Your Asian Story. From artists and entrepreneurs to mental health experts and academics, each of these incredible women has a powerful story to share and their strength and resilience is reflected in their art and work. 

Let’s honour their courage to share their stories and be part of this incredible community. They are a beautiful reminder that our stories matter and that we are all capable of so much. 

With much love and respect ❤️💛🧡

@chefkatiechin @michellieart @kalikayap @janehfromjersey @thesassyasiantherapist @cynthia.midori @zoehong @jesslall33 @veronicazund @maechandran @jingle1223 @becmorris @jeniegao @sketchpoetic @esther_tow @sketchykarr 

You can find the interviews with all of these amazing women in the @shareyourasianstory feed. 

#ShareYourAsianStory #iwd2023 #internationalwomensday #watercolorportraits #asianwomen #sandrahsuart

Watercolor artist Sandra Hsu (@sandrahsuart ) focuses in abstract art, fashion illustration, and portraiture.
Sandra co-founded Share Your Asian Story (SYAS), an Instagram account dedicated to telling Asian experiences to combat anti-Asian racism, in 2021 with Marcus Kan of Draw a Dot and two other Asian artists. Every two weeks, Sandra welcomes members of the Asian diaspora to discuss what it's like to live in a location and culture that are different from their own. The Share Your Asian Story collection is made up of the portraits she painted of these visitors.
In her own work, Sandra is enthralled by exploring the virtually limitless potential of watercolor. 

If you want to see more of her artwork, join us in our Dreams of the Dragon event! 

Follow @creativoofficial for event updates!

This Sunday on @shareyourasianstory , we’re thrilled to welcome Elenor Mak, founder of @hellojillybing ! 

Elenor Mak is the proud founder of Jilly Bing, a company that's pioneering creating dolls and toys that accurately represent Asian American children and their culture. Elenor began this mission after a disappointing search for a doll that looked like her daughter. Rather than accept the status quo, Elenor did what she has done her entire career: She created something from nothing.

Elenor hopes that through Jilly Bing, every Asian American child will see themselves in the dolls and toys that they hold, and feel a deep sense of pride about who they are. 

She lives in San Francisco with Richard, her husband and their two young children, James and Jilian, who probably believe they have a third sibling named Jilly Bing.

#shareyourasianstory #asianrepresentation #entrepreneur #aapiheritagemonth #asianamericangirl

This Sunday on Share Your Asian Story, we are so honored to have  dancer/choreographer Cecilia Wen, affectionately known as Cece @eazycece_ and founder of @moveintouch , as our very special guest! Please join our hosts @sandrahsuart @the_illustrienne and @beck_lines this Sunday July 9  at 1pm PST as they ask Cece to share her Asian Story!❤️💛🧡

Cecilia Wen, born and raised in Shanghai, China, made the life-changing decision to move to Los Angeles, California for college at the age of 18. Unbeknownst to her at the time, this move would pave the way for a fulfilling career in teaching and mentoring, utilizing movement as a powerful tool. Cecilia's passion for dancing and teaching led her down this path, but it was through years of unwavering dedication and hard work that she not only developed herself as a dancer and choreographer, but also discovered her true identity as an artist and individual.

Cecilia believes that her relatability stems from her own personal journey. Every mindset she preaches, every thought she expresses, and every tip she provides, she has experienced firsthand. She has fought her way to become the secure, strong, and confident woman and dancer that she is today. Recognizing that personal growth outside of the dance room greatly influences one's abilities as a mover, Cecilia founded Move In Touch. This platform encourages individuals to move with intention and use movement as a means to connect with their inner selves. 

🎨: @sandrahsuart 

#shareyourasianstory #asianamerican #chineseamerican #asiancreativity

This Sunday at 1pm PST on Share Your Asian Story, we are so honored to have ground-breaking skincare entrepreneur Janice Buu @janice_kanaskincare as our very special guest! 

Janice is a serial entrepreneur in the CBD space, previously a behavioral therapist for children with developmental disorders. After witnessing her 3 year old patient's drastic improvement with cannabis use (dosed by her own mother), she became an advocate for cannabis and founded her female empowering brand Kana Skincare at the age of 24.

With an innate talent in entrepreneurship and people skills, Janice grew up in a business environment since age 3, went on her first solo 'work trip' at 7, and took over leadership roles in every stage of her life. Marie Claire named her the woman to watch in the CBD space due to Kana Skincare's success in a nationwide launch within 3 months and internationally within its first 6 months. Recognized by Forbes, Wall Street Journal, Allure, New Beauty, Vogue, South China Morning Post, award winning TV shows and Netflix/HBO series, her creative concepts have shaped new standards in the industry and everyday lifestyle.

Aside from spending time carrying out unique concepts, turning ideas into reality, Janice likes to mentor other female entrepreneurs, host beauty and wellness events, solo travel, read, and dance! 

Join me, @beck_lines and @the_illustrienne this Sunday as we ask Janice to share her Asian Story!

#shareyourasianstory #asianamerican #asianentrepreneur #girlboss #beautyentrepreneur

This Sunday on Share Your Asian Story, we are honored to host Chinese-American TV and podcast host, producer Yue “Yosemite” Xu @nonplatonic ! ❤️💛🧡

Yue's journey began in Beijing, where she was always the entertainer in her family, often putting on shows and skits for her relatives. She moved to the US at the age of 8 and initially pursued a career in commercial dance. Feeling the need for a more sustainable path, she transitioned to a corporate job but soon felt the call to become a TV host. Her hosting reel caught the attention of a big agency, leading to numerous hosting gigs. 

During a family visit to Beijing that was supposed to last only two weeks, Yue landed a regular TV spot, which led her to stay for two years! While in Beijing, she worked for state-owned media, where she witnessed firsthand the power of propaganda. She then became a regular host on a tech show and traveled China and eventually the UK, experiencing new technologies and inventions. 

Yue’s passion for entertainment and tech led her to San Francisco, where she produced a LIVE trivia show, created brand stories for startups, and became a talent producer at fitness tech company Tonal.

Yue also co-created “Dateable”, a podcast about modern dating that became a New York Times featured podcast, leading to a spinoff series. Recently moving to LA, she continues her pursuits in fitness tech, podcasting, commercials, tennis, and has a secret project in the works, all while being the best dog mom she can be. 

Please join @sandrahsuart , @the_illustrienne and @beck_lines at 1pm PST on Sunday as we ask Yue to share her Asian Story. 

#shareyourasianstory #podcaster #asianamerican

After so many years, I’m officially the grizzled veteran of @ladancefit Dance Team performances. 😉✌️

This Sunday at Dec. 10 at 1pm, we are excited to have Alcina Tran @iamalcina as our guest on Share Your Asian Story!❤️💛🧡

Alcina Tran is the pioneering founder of Soulful of Life, a collective dedicated to holistic healing through coaching, sound and energy healing and soul integrative practices. As a child of immigrant parents and a first generation Vietnamese Cambodian American, she is on a mission to promote generational healing, supporting first-gen entrepreneurs and creatives overcome inherited limitations for emotional, financial and soul freedom. In addition to being an ICF-Certified Coach, Alcina is an independent artist, who creates conscious music for global healing and love.

Please join me, along with my cohosts @the_illustrienne and @beck_lines as we ask Alcina to share her Asian story!

🎨 @sandrahsuart
